🚀 Day 2/30 – LeetCode C++ Challenge
🔹 Problem: Reverse String (Easy)
🔹 Approach Used: Two Pointers

💡 Problem Explanation:
Given a string (or character array), reverse it in-place using minimal extra space.

📝 Solution Using Two Pointers
cpp
Copy
Edit
void reverseString(vector<char>& s) {
    int left = 0, right = s.size() - 1;
    while (left < right) {
        swap(s[left], s[right]);
        left++;
        right--;
    }
}
✅ Efficient Approach:
✔ Swaps first & last characters, moves pointers inward.
✔ Time Complexity: O(N)
✔ Space Complexity: O(1) (In-place reversal).
